The paper deals with the planted coloring problem, which is a well-studied problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). It also involves the analysis of algorithms for the problem, which falls under computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of expanders and regular graphs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper involves the study of hardness results, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS).
